item.description:
Definition
A "net open position" is the difference between a company's total assets and liabilities in a specific foreign currency, which measures its exposure to foreign exchange (FX) risk.
&nbsp;It can also refer to the net difference between the total volume of long and short positions for a single financial instrument in a trading account.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The net open position helps in understanding potential profit or loss from currency fluctuations

Definition
A settlement agent facilitates the transfer of ownership of a property from a seller to a buyer, handling the legal and administrative details of the transaction.&nbsp;They are also known as&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1GCEA_enZA1171ZA1171&amp;cs=0&amp;sca_esv=06680e941bb4b5b6&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifPFDCH914CsCcGiWIeXSp4ng8HntQ%3A1760463102805&amp;q=conveyancers&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjJ3daOnKSQAxXBUkEAHTNvApEQxccNegQIAxAB&amp;mstk=AUtExfB-vUV196sGQGYVC3ULIbeSb8Yz6uPEofP0k8072OEaWmFi2UfrwmqK0_Cs5s9XHptc7fAki0qHFD0k4m2vI3gZYZNbcTFa2x8Cvnc7NVPG4q7_hv4LhVkwEXsLJmQkv-EQxCqbw-PjEoynWJsuXu1rYz-b42LdMaVCIXOtCtFIBUM&amp;csui=3" rel="noopener nofollow" class="external-link is-unresolved" href="https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1GCEA_enZA1171ZA1171&amp;cs=0&amp;sca_esv=06680e941bb4b5b6&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifPFDCH914CsCcGiWIeXSp4ng8HntQ%3A1760463102805&amp;q=conveyancers&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjJ3daOnKSQAxXBUkEAHTNvApEQxccNegQIAxAB&amp;mstk=AUtExfB-vUV196sGQGYVC3ULIbeSb8Yz6uPEofP0k8072OEaWmFi2UfrwmqK0_Cs5s9XHptc7fAki0qHFD0k4m2vI3gZYZNbcTFa2x8Cvnc7NVPG4q7_hv4LhVkwEXsLJmQkv-EQxCqbw-PjEoynWJsuXu1rYz-b42LdMaVCIXOtCtFIBUM&amp;csui=3" target="_self">conveyancers</a>&nbsp;and coordinate paperwork, such as transfer documents and mortgage files, liaise with financial institutions, and ensure all legal requirements and conditions are met.&nbsp;In a broader financial context, a settlement agent can also refer to a financial institution that handles the transfer of securities.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Role in property transactions Manages legal transfer:&nbsp; They ensure all legal requirements for transferring property title are met and that the new owner's title is registered correctly.&nbsp; Handles paperwork:&nbsp; They prepare and manage all necessary documents, including transfer and stamp duty forms.&nbsp; Coordinates funds:&nbsp; They liaise with banks and brokers to ensure funds are transferred correctly to meet deadlines.&nbsp; Verifies property status:&nbsp; They perform searches to verify ownership and check for encumbrances or liens on the property.&nbsp; Ensures conditions are met:&nbsp; They verify that all inspections and special conditions in the contract have been completed.&nbsp; Negotiates issues:&nbsp; They can negotiate on your behalf if any issues arise during the settlement process.&nbsp; Role in financial settlements Facilitates security transfer:&nbsp; In the financial markets, a settlement agent can be a person or an institution that arranges the transfer of securities.&nbsp; <br>Manages risk:&nbsp; In the national payment system, like the one run by the&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1GCEA_enZA1171ZA1171&amp;cs=0&amp;sca_esv=06680e941bb4b5b6&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifPFDCH914CsCcGiWIeXSp4ng8HntQ%3A1760463102805&amp;q=South+African+Reserve+Bank&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjJ3daOnKSQAxXBUkEAHTNvApEQxccNegQINhAB&amp;mstk=AUtExfB-vUV196sGQGYVC3ULIbeSb8Yz6uPEofP0k8072OEaWmFi2UfrwmqK0_Cs5s9XHptc7fAki0qHFD0k4m2vI3gZYZNbcTFa2x8Cvnc7NVPG4q7_hv4LhVkwEXsLJmQkv-EQxCqbw-PjEoynWJsuXu1rYz-b42LdMaVCIXOtCtFIBUM&amp;csui=3" rel="noopener nofollow" class="external-link is-unresolved" href="https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1GCEA_enZA1171ZA1171&amp;cs=0&amp;sca_esv=06680e941bb4b5b6&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifPFDCH914CsCcGiWIeXSp4ng8HntQ%3A1760463102805&amp;q=South+African+Reserve+Bank&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjJ3daOnKSQAxXBUkEAHTNvApEQxccNegQINhAB&amp;mstk=AUtExfB-vUV196sGQGYVC3ULIbeSb8Yz6uPEofP0k8072OEaWmFi2UfrwmqK0_Cs5s9XHptc7fAki0qHFD0k4m2vI3gZYZNbcTFa2x8Cvnc7NVPG4q7_hv4LhVkwEXsLJmQkv-EQxCqbw-PjEoynWJsuXu1rYz-b42LdMaVCIXOtCtFIBUM&amp;csui=3" target="_self">South African Reserve Bank</a>,&nbsp;a settlement agent acts as an intermediary that enables financial institutions to make payments to each other.&nbsp; Handles settlement risk:&nbsp; This role also involves managing the risk that a buyer or seller might not meet their obligations, which could cause the transaction to fail. E.g. Strate, Euroclear, Clearstream
